16/11/2008
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The BiH's prosecutor's office has charged former Bosniak military commander Naser Oric with extortion and illegal possession of weapons and explosives, media reported on Friday (November 14th). 
Oric allegedly extorted 120,000 euros from another individual, said the chief of the Sarajevo cantonal prosecution, Branko Sljivar. 
Last July, The Hague war crimes tribunal acquitted Oric of "murder and inhumane treatment of Serb prisoners" during his forces' defence of Srebrenica. 
(Fena, Reuters, AFP, B92 - 14/11/08)
